storyInfo: The onslaught of mutants challenges the operators defending the Lord's Manor. Operator Tachanka resolves to defend the others so that they may find shelter, standing alone against the swarm.

attributes.content: How many of these *profanity* things did they make?!
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Give me a hand, Miss Lord!
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Mr. Occphen! What are you doing here?
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: How could I just wait around down there? I'm a Rhodes Island Operator too!
attributes.name: Occphen

attributes.content: Damn straight! You really saved us!
attributes.name: Liskarm

attributes.content: Get ready to blow the engine...
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: They've been pushed back, for now. But they'll come for us again before long.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: There... seems to be less of them?
attributes.name: Frost

attributes.content: I'm all out of 'welcome mats'. Ammo's gone too.
attributes.name: Frost

attributes.content: Get to the shelter! Take the Rhodes Island Operators and get to shelter!
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: I'm tired of all the hiding and running.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Running can't win you the war. History's shown.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: When they pull weapons on the Infected and try to kill my friends, it's a war.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: I've been through plenty of wars in my time.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: If I can kill even one more *profanity* monster here, it'll give the townsfolk a better shot at survival.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: I'll make my stand here until I run out of ammo. Until the very end.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: The battle's not over. How could I retreat?
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: You're the one who says not to play hero!
attributes.name: Frost

attributes.content: I don't think I'm playing hero, Tina.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: I'm just doing the right thing.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: No matter what happens, the show ends here, today.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: It was always going to turn out like this. We all knew it, from the moment you decided to stay and fight.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: I'll stay behind and help the warrior hold them back. And if things go bad, I'll cover his retreat.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: An Originium bomb I tried my hand at making. There's only two left.
attributes.name: Frost

attributes.content: You didn't tell her the truth. You're not going to run.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Hahaha... You didn't have to go blowing this old man's scheme.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: You need someone to hold these monsters back.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.text: The aged ranger takes out a blade.

attributes.content: The old Lord's blade. I borrowed it.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: This is a fine blade. The old Lord had good taste.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: Beautifully decorated steel, and a hand-lain turquoise handle that's as nice as any modern industrially-manufactured weapon.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: It's a lot safer to stand in the back with a bow and arrow than fighting on the front line.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.text: The old Savra ranger dances with his long, curved blade.

attributes.content: I'm so much older and slower than I was.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: But the blade, she's as sharp as ever.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: I still don't know your name, warrior.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: I should tell you my name too.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: But the sands buried my name the day we stained the valley red with blood, along with the past.
attributes.name: Rangers

attributes.content: You decided to stay and fight. That's what matters.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: 'They told me I'd died. They were wrong. I was reborn. '
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: No matter how many of those monsters there are.
attributes.name: Tachanka
